				"content" : "<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<!-- Thie example adapted from the PET Handbook, copyright University of Cambridge ESOL Examinations -->\n<assessmentItem xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1\"\n                xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n                xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1 http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqti_v2p1.xsd\"\n                title=\"\" adaptive=\"false\" timeDependent=\"false\">\n\n<responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_01\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"identifier\">\n        <correctResponse>\n            <value>ChoiceB</value>\n        </correctResponse>\n    </responseDeclaration>\n    <outcomeDeclaration identifier=\"SCORE\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"integer\">\n        <defaultValue>\n            <value>0</value>\n        </defaultValue>\n    </outcomeDeclaration>\n\n<responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_02\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"identifier\">\n        <correctResponse>\n            <value>ChoiceD</value>\n        </correctResponse>\n    </responseDeclaration>\n    <outcomeDeclaration identifier=\"SCORE\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"integer\">\n        <defaultValue>\n            <value>0</value>\n        </defaultValue>\n    </outcomeDeclaration>\n\n<responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_03\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"identifier\">\n        <correctResponse>\n            <value>ChoiceB</value>\n        </correctResponse>\n    </responseDeclaration>\n    <outcomeDeclaration identifier=\"SCORE\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"integer\">\n        <defaultValue>\n            <value>0</value>\n        </defaultValue>\n    </outcomeDeclaration>\n    \n    <responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_04\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"identifier\">\n        <correctResponse>\n            <value></value>\n        </correctResponse>\n    </responseDeclaration>\n    <outcomeDeclaration identifier=\"SCORE\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"integer\">\n        <defaultValue>\n            <value>0</value>\n        </defaultValue>\n    </outcomeDeclaration>\n\n    <!-- an Extended text entry response for longer form text entry -->\n    <responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_05\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"string\"/>\n\n   <responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_06\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"identifier\">\n        <correctResponse>\n            <value></value>\n        </correctResponse>\n    </responseDeclaration>\n    <outcomeDeclaration identifier=\"SCORE\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"integer\">\n        <defaultValue>\n            <value>0</value>\n        </defaultValue>\n    </outcomeDeclaration>\n\n    <!-- an Extended text entry response for longer form text entry -->\n    <responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_07\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"string\"/>\n\n    <!-- an Extended text entry response for longer form text entry -->\n    <responseDeclaration identifier=\"Q_08\" cardinality=\"single\" baseType=\"string\"/>\n\n    <itemBody>\n\n\n        <resource\n                type=\"passage\"\n                title=\"The Driver\"\n                copyrightOwner=\"Renny Christopher\"\n                />\n\n        <h1 class=\"para-center\" >The Driver</h1>\n       \n       <center class=\"passage-author\">Renny Christopher</center>\n        \n<p>The best time was the mornings</p>\n<p>when the job was far away.</p>\n<p>Dad and I carried our coffee to the truck,</p>\n<p>rode up the crowded highway, quiet,</p>\n<p>Dad driving in his sleep, <b>[5]</b></p>\n<p>threading traffic in a dream.</p>\n<br></br>\n<p>Once at the job we parked and woke up</p>\n<p>from the freeway dream</p>\n<p>took the tools from the lockbox in the back.</p>\n<p>At lunch we ate in the truckbed <b>[10]</b></p>\n<p>spare tire and rope coils for our chairs.</p>\n<br></br>\n<p>On the way home, Dad would talk,</p>\n<p>telling stories of the war he was in</p>\n<p>--the good war he called it--</p>\n<p>or of driving midget race cars [15]</p>\n<p>on tracks all up and down California.</p>\n<p>He told stories of highways he drove</p>\n<p>towing his racecar along--</p>\n<p>the old road over the Cuesta grade,</p>\n<p>the Coast highway to Long Beach [20]</p>\n<p>roads to anywhere that had a dirt track.</p>\n<br></br>\n<p>As he talked he drove one-handed--</p>\n<p>left hand on the wheel, elbow out the window</p>\n<p>in his right hand a bottle of pop</p>\n<p>right foot on the accelerator. [25]</p>\n<br></br>\n<p>Once, he asked me to drive home.</p>\n<p>As I glanced at him in the passenger seat</p>\n<p>I could see in the sunlight through the windshield</p>\n<p>his temples just beginning to go gray.</p>\n\n<div class=\"note-tip\">Taken from <i>Longing Fervently for Revolution</i> Renny Christopher/Slipstream Press</div><p/>\n\n<hr class=\"element-seperator\"/>\n\n<choiceInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_01\" shuffle=\"false\" maxChoices=\"1\">\n            <prompt>The tone of the poem reveals what about the speaker?</prompt>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceA\">The speaker is angry about the past.</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceB\">The speaker is sentimental about the past.</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceC\">The speaker is proud of the past.</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceD\">The speaker is disgusted by the past.</simpleChoice>\n        </choiceInteraction>\n\n\n<choiceInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_02\" shuffle=\"false\" maxChoices=\"1\">\n        <prompt>What literary device is used in lines 5-6?</prompt>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceA\">Simile</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceB\">Metaphor</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceC\">Personification</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceD\">Hyperbole</simpleChoice>\n        </choiceInteraction>\n        \n        \n<choiceInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_03\" shuffle=\"false\" maxChoices=\"1\">\n            <prompt>In the last line of the poem the speaker uses the phrase “his temples just beginning to go gray” to represent</prompt>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceA\">his fears for his father</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceB\">the passage of time</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceC\">the highs and lows of the father’s life</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceD\">the darkness in his relationship with his father</simpleChoice>\n        </choiceInteraction>\n        \n        \n<choiceInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_04\" shuffle=\"false\" maxChoices=\"1\">\n        <prompt>Both the speaker and the father enjoy their work days together.</prompt>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceA\">True</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceB\">False</simpleChoice>\n        </choiceInteraction>\n\n\n<p class=\"prompt\">Explain your choice by using specific details from the poem.</p>\n<extendedTextInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_05\" expectedLength=\"200\" class=\"answer_5_linebox\"></extendedTextInteraction>\n\n\n<choiceInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_06\" shuffle=\"false\" maxChoices=\"1\">\n            <prompt>The father teaches the speaker that dreaming is better than doing.</prompt>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceA\">True</simpleChoice>\n            <simpleChoice identifier=\"ChoiceB\">False</simpleChoice>\n        </choiceInteraction>\n        \n<p class=\"prompt\">Explain your choice by using specific details from poem.</p>\n    <extendedTextInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_07\" expectedLength=\"200\" class=\"answer_5_linebox\"></extendedTextInteraction>\n\n<p class=\"prompt\">Explain, by using specific details from the poem, how “The Driver” explores the role of memory to characterize relationships.</p>\n    <extendedTextInteraction responseIdentifier=\"Q_08\" expectedLength=\"200\" class=\"answer_5_linebox\"></extendedTextInteraction>\n    </itemBody>\n</assessmentItem>"
			}
